This paper deals with fair optimization and learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the creation of fair models that adhere to data privacy guarantees, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of "Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also mentions statistical definitions of algorithmic fairness, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of empirical risk minimization algorithms, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of "Computational Complexity" (cs.CY).
